In a speech marking the 70th anniversary of the North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO), Vice President Mike Pence emphasized the strength of the alliance under President Donald Trump's leadership. He highlighted the progress made in strengthening the US military, including increased defense spending and modernization efforts. Pence also called on NATO allies, particularly Germany, to fulfill their commitments to spend at least 2% of their GDP on defense. He expressed concern over Germany's reliance on Russia for energy and its decision to purchase a Russian missile system, warning that it could harm the alliance. Pence also mentioned the challenge of China's rise and the need for NATO members to address the implications of China's expanding influence. Overall, he emphasized the importance of unity and shared principles in maintaining the strength and effectiveness of NATO.